section.section:
"Public record" means the original or any copy of any documentary material that:
is made by a unit or instrumentality of the State government or of a political subdivision or received by the unit or instrumentality in connection with the transaction of public business; and
is in any form, including:
a card;
a computerized record;
correspondence;
a drawing;
film or microfilm;
a form;
a map;
a photograph or photostat;
a recording; or
a tape.
